article.headline: Morehead St. 57, W. Illinois 56
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Quentin Pryor scored 11 points, including the game-winning layup with 0.4 seconds remaining, to lead Morehead State to a 57-56 win over Western Illinois. The Eagles (3-3) led 51-40 with 9:18 remaining, but went scoreless for the next 7:33 to let the Leathernecks back into the game. Morehead State never trailed by more than a point over the final two minutes. Shaun Williams and Cordaryl Ballard joined Pryor in double figures with 10 points apiece for Morehead State. Both teams struggled offensively, as the Eagles shot 41.8 percent from the field, including 2-for-17 from 3-point range. Western Illinois shot 38 percent from the floor and hit 6-of-20 3-pointers. David Jackson paced Western Illinois (2-4) with 10 points and 10 rebounds, both team-highs. His final points came on two free throws with seven seconds remaining, setting the stage for Pryor's winning basket.
